<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Berlese mentions that he collected many specimens, especially in moss on roofs in Venice, Florence, Naples, etc. I collected indeed specimens on a roof in Florence; they can be regarded as topotypes. The identity of the common species is certain.</paragraph>
